a ton of spanish with a lot of work
Spanish 120 continues from where Spanish 110 left off.
The part that you take after L1. It's basically the same class, just farther along. M-F is rough, but it's 1.5 credits.

Spanish 120 is a natural progression from Spanish 110. The level of difficult does not go up, but there is a bit more to memorize in terms of vocab and tenses. As long as you take the time to memorize these things, you'll do fine in the course.

Spanish 120 continues Spanish 110 but explores more difficult grammatical situations and lots of vocab is added.Would recommend to any student interested in spanish. Workload isn't too hard, and is manageable.
Not a bad course, however very demanding and exponentially more difficult than spanish 110.
